maml:description.maml:para: Provides a way to expand collections in an object property prior to being sent to Export-Csv.

Using a predefined set of properties to display ($Output), data is collected from the Win32_NetworkAdapterConfiguration class and then passed to the Convert-OutputForCSV funtion which expands any property with a collection so it can be read properly prior to being sent to Export-Csv. Properties that had a collection will be viewed as a stack in the spreadsheet.
Requires -Version 3.0

maml:Description.maml:para: The object that will be sent to Export-Csv
This determines whether the property that has the collection will be shown in the CSV as a comma delimmited string or as a stacked string.
The object that will be sent to Export-Csv
This determines whether the property that has the collection will be shown in the CSV as a comma delimmited string or as a stacked string.

maml:alert.maml:para: Name: Convert-OutputForCSV Author: Boe Prox Created: 24 Jan 2014 Version History: 1.1 - 02 Feb 2014 -Removed OutputOrder parameter as it is no longer needed; inputobject order is now respected in the output object 1.0 - 24 Jan 2014 -Initial Creation

dev:remarks.maml:para: Get-WMIObject -Class Win32_NetworkAdapterConfiguration -Filter "IPEnabled='True'" | Select-Object $Output | Convert-OutputForCSV | Export-Csv -NoTypeInformation -Path NIC.csv
